Eye of Horus review.text:
Eye of Horus is themed around ancient Egyptian mythology.
Players will travel far into the past and discover a world of mysterious gods. As players explore the treasures of Egypt, they will need to hope the god Horus stays favorable.
This slot will particularly suit fans of ancient history.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The soundtrack uses an intense drumbeat to give Eye of Horus a dramatic atmosphere. Didgeridoo notes also help to create an otherworldly vibe that suits the mythological theme.
Vivid blue scarab beetle, black jackals, and ornate fans are all among the symbols. Each image is illustrated in a minimalist style that brings to mind ancient hieroglyphics. Meanwhile, lower-paying symbols are rendered in vivid jewel tones including red, blue, and green.
Behind the reels, players will glimpse ancient stone architecture. A palette of warm browns and golds brings to mind a sunset in the desert.
Overall, the soundtrack and animation create an entrancing world of ancient Egyptian fantasy.

Gameplay.text:
Eye of Horus is a classic five-reel, three-row slot, with ten win lines.
The game offers players a typical slot experience with click-to-play gameplay that feels as old as the pyramids and a free spin bonus to spice things up. It is nothing too special but if it ain’t broke, don’t fix it!

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except for the Bonus symbol.
The Bonus symbol acts as a scatter, paying out for two or more symbols anywhere on the reels. However, it also triggers the Free Spin Bonus should the player land three or more.
The Free Spin Bonus game gives the player 12 free spins at their current bet amount.
During the free spins, landing a Bonus symbol will give the player an Upgrade Tablet, gaining the player an extra free spin. Landing two or three Upgrade Tablets earns the player 3 and 5 extra free spins respectively.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.31%, above our yardstick for an average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
Medium-high volatility makes the Eye of Horus slot a moderately good match for our preferred slot machine strategies.
Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility and RTP, so moderately high in both isn’t a bad option.

Conclusion.text:
We recommend this high RTP, medium-high volatility, ancient Egyptian mythology-themed slot.
With decent graphics and bonuses, Eye of Horus is a solid selection, especially for fans of ancient history.
Mathematically-minded players will be reasonably pleased by this slot’s combination of an ample RTP and moderately high volatility.

title: Mustang Money
overview:
Mustang Money
    
        Play Mustang Money demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Ugly outside and in, avoid this slot and its 94.38% RTP.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The Wilds of the American West make for a common slot theme. So a slot needs to do something interesting with it, if they’re going to stand out. Mustang Money does not.
There are cactuses, a neon horse, an ugly landscape of monument valley and some copy-pasted Ace to Jack symbols.
Ainsworth's Mustang Money gets an F for effort.

media.caption: High symbol wins even with stacked wilds are too small

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
As well as having an unimaginative theme, Mustang Money executes that theme hideously. The entire slot is done in murky reds and oranges that look grubby and remind the player of clotting blood rather than the desert sunset they are clearly trying to emulate.
The sound effects are cheaply rendered horse beats and a panicked mare. Hardly evocative of the noble mustang. And there is no music track to speak of.
The animations cap the wholly nasty affair with cheap boxy win lines and little else that moves.

Gameplay.text:
Mustang Money is a five reel slot with three rows. It also has a ridiculous 100 win lines, which on a five by three slot results in small three in a row wins chucking out three or four wins at once.
It is not clear that this is preferable to higher wins on fewer winlines, though it doesn’t reduce the volatility, which is good for our strategies.
It has a simple free spin bonus and no gamble feature. So a straightforward game in all respects.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol and appears only on 3 rightmost reels.
Three or more Scatters trigger a Free Spin bonus with 10 Free Spins.
During Free Spins, an additional Multiplier Wild is added to the reels. The Multiplier Wild appears only on reels two and four. This multiplier is randomly assigned. On reel two it can be either x1 or x2. On reel four it is x1 to x5 inclusive.
Free Spins can be retriggered.

media.alt: Mustang Money free spins wilds win
media.caption: Win with both Wild symbols in the free spins bonus game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 94.38%, way below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%. An RTP this dire would kill a slot’s chances of getting a recommendation dead on its own, even without Mustang Money’s other problems.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€1.00, if you play all 100 lines, up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin. That minimum bet is very high for a small stakes player who would be forced to play fewer lines if they want a more reasonable bet size.
The volatility of this game is medium-high, which would make it a moderately good match for our preferred slot machine strategies, if it had a much better RTP. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Paytable for high symbols of the Mustang Money slot

Conclusions.text:
Visually, Mustang Money is a bit of a mess. Not disastrously so, but mildly ugly and thematically inconsistent.
Problem is, that from that poor first impression there is no turning point. The gameplay is basic and uninteresting, the minimum bet is absurdly high. The bonus doesn’t add much and the volatility is okay but at the very lowest end of tolerable.
And then there is the RTP. 94.38% is far too low. Anything under 96% is poor. Below 95% is just mean spirited. Give this slot a wide berth.

title: Buffalo Rising Megaways
overview:
Buffalo Rising Megaways
    
        Play Buffalo Rising Megaways demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Follow the migrating buffalo in this American wildlife themed slot which sports medium-high volatility and an RTP of 96.50%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The great plains of North America were once inhabited by millions of buffalo roaming in vast herds that numbered in the tens of thousands. None of them had the glowing red eyes of the bison depicted here in Buffalo Rising Megaways, however, or they might have frightened off the hunters that nearly drove them to extinction.
The other fauna depicted in Buffalo Rising Megaways are more accurately presented, with ordinary limpid or dark eyes. The enormous moose, the majestic bear, the lithe and clever wolf.
These are the symbols of the American wilds which Buffalo Rising Megaways intends to evoke, and if you’re a fan of American wildlife, this might appeal to you.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The creatures are drawn nicely in the spray-painted mural style that all American wildlife themed slots have borrowed from one another. Though here the visuals are rather less annoying than in other slots that have been done in this style.
In fact, when coupled with the clean animation style and pleasant music, sound effects, and win sounds, the whole slot has a decidedly charming tone.

media.caption: Big win in the Buffalo Rising Megaways slot

Gameplay.text:
Buffalo Rising Megaways uses the Megaways system. This system has six reels, with each reel having between one and seven symbols on it. The exact number of symbols is decided at random on each spin.
Instead of using winlines, winning combinations are made up of any sequence of symbols on consecutive reels starting from reel one. This system results in up to 117,649 ways to win.
There is also a cascade mechanic and a Mystery symbol, which transforms into any symbol except the Scatter once it lands, adding a second layer of tension to each spin.
The cascade occurs after wins are calculated. The winning symbols are removed and new symbols fall down from above to take their place. Wins are then recalculated and any additional cascades occur if there are any new winning combinations.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Four or more Scatter symbols will trigger the Free Spin bonus. The Free Spin bonus comes in three flavours, each of which has a different volatility. They either start with: 15 free spins with a starting multiplier of x10, 10 spins with x5, or 5 spins with x10. Additional Scatters above four award additional spins.
There is also a Mystery bonus that awards a randomised starting multiplier and a randomised number of spins. The multiplier increases by one with every winning spin.
Players can buy directly into the bonus round using the Buffalo Bet option, which is priced at 100x the bet per spin.

media.caption: There is an option to choose a mystery choice within the Free Spins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.50%, nicely over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€10.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium to high, which makes it a reasonable match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility, and although a higher RTP would be preferable, 96.50% is perfectly acceptable for this level of volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Buffalo Rising Megaways slot machine

Conclusion.text:
With its pleasing graphics, atmospheric sound and clean animation, Buffalo Rising Megaways makes a good first impression.
We’d prefer a little more oomph in the volatility department but medium-high is not bad, especially when coupled with the above average RTP and exciting bonus features.
This slot has our recommendation.

about_game: A delightful dragon-themed, grid-based slot machine with an RTP or 96.46% and high volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Dragon eggs are the main feature of DragonFall. Each egg is beautifully designed to look shiny and Game of Thrones-like. The large grid is reminiscent a little of matching games like Candy Crush. These associations are clearly deliberate design choices, pushing it towards a blended look: a gamified fantasy land.
If you enjoy seeking treasures deep beneath the earth where dragons nest on hoards of loot, then this might be the game for you.

media.caption: Win with a Wild symbol with multiplier

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
DragonFall’s graphics are excellent, a pleasant background of treasure is lit by animated dragon flames.
The animations are smooth and clear and work well with the pseudo-3D look that the design team settled on. The elements are all elegantly and intelligently designed.
The music for DragonFall owes a lot to great fantasy soundtracks filled as it is with bass drums and chanting voices. It serves perfectly to create the high-fantasy atmosphere that the setting demands.

media.caption: Win in the base game

Gameplay.text:
DragonFall is played on an eight by eight grid. Symbols fall from above and five or more identical symbols connected to each other vertically and/or horizontally result in a winning cluster. The more symbols there are in a winning cluster, the bigger the win.
There is a cascade feature in which winning symbols are removed from the board and all symbols fall down with empty spaces at the top being filled by new symbols. These cascades continue until there are no more winning combinations on the board.
There is also a Colossal Symbol Modifier. This modifier feature can appear at any time and expands a random symbol to take up a larger block of symbols. Wilds cannot be converted by this modifier but all other symbols can.

media.caption: Randomly appearing feature - Colossal Symbol Modifier
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols. The Wild also pays out like a scatter symbol and three or more Wilds anywhere on the reels trigger the free spin bonus.
When a Wild is part of a winning cluster, instead of being removed during the cascade, the Wild simply moves to an adjacent spot on the grid then stays in place when the other symbols drop.
Wilds also apply the current active multiplier to any win they are part of. Once a win is calculated, the multiplier is increased by one.
If the player uses the Bonus Bet, the next spin is guaranteed to include at least three Wilds and will trigger the Bonus game.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.46%, well over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€10.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a great match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Paytable for DragonFall slot

title: Eye of Horus Megaways
overview:

about_game: This slot should be buried deeper than a mummy’s grave with its low RTP (95.47%) and medium volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Hieroglyphics and a gloomy temple setting immediately catapult this slot into the generic obscurity of dozens of other Ancient Egyptian slot machines.
It doesn’t bring much new to the table. No modern adventurers dead set on tomb raiding. No artistic flourishes to the hieroglyph designs. In fact, it seems to have taken away many of the things that make Egyptian slots interesting to look at.
When a theme is done as many times as this one, you need to try harder than Eye of Horus Megaways to stand out.

media.alt: Eye of Horus Megaways free spins upgrade feature
media.caption: Eye of Horus Megaways free spins upgrade feature

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Unusually for a maker that has sprung for the license on the Megaways system, the graphics on this slot are pretty unimpressive. Decent, but unimaginative, renderings of Egyptian images.
The animations are perfectly acceptable, but lack flare and character. Which is also true of the soundtrack. The win and spin sounds appear to have been grandfathered in from other BluePrint Gaming slots and are utterly without atmosphere or style.
This like of customisation can work with some themes, but in an Ancient Egyptian slot such things contrast with the tone of the game and end up throwing the player off.

Gameplay.text:
The Megaways system comes from Big Time Gaming. This system randomises the number of symbols on each reel every spin. It also uses an any way wins system where wins are counted from left to right starting on reel one, regardless of where on the reels the matching symbols land.
The number of win ways changes spin to spin. Though it is always between a minimum of 64 (two symbols per reel) and a maximum of 15,625 (for five symbols on each reel).
The free spin bonus has some fun "upgrades" built into it (see below for details). All in all this adds up to some quality gameplay that makes up somewhat for the slots many other failings.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. When a Wild lands, it expands to fill its entire reel.
Three or more Scatters trigger twelve free spins.
During the Free Spins, each Wild that lands on any reel adds an upgrade tablet for the remaining spins. The first upgrade tablet turns all of the lowest paying symbols into the second lowest paying symbols. The second upgrade upgrades them all to the third lowest. Etc...
Additionally, each Wild that lands awards the player more spins. One spin for one Wild. Two Wilds in the same spin add three spins to the player's total. Three Wilds at once add five spins. And four Wilds add seven.

media.alt: Eye of Horus Megaways free spins win
media.caption: Wins are going up with each wild symbol hit and following an upgrade

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.49%, coming in well under our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€10.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a poor match for 
our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility. Coupled with a low RTP, this excludes this slot from getting our recommendation.

media.alt: Eye of Horus Megaways full paytable
media.caption: Full paytable for Eye of Horus Megaways slot

Conclusion.text:
If bland theme and visuals, with borrowed sound effects and animations do little to enamour us with this slot – then the low RTP and medium volatility hammer the nails into the slot’s sarcophagus.
Some solid gameplay mechanics and a good bonus game are not enough to make up for that.
It should be noted that, although we do not recommend this slot, it has proved popular. So be aware that your mileage may vary.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Rick and Morty Megaways follow the high-concept sci-fi shenanigans of the world’s smartest psychopath and his idiot grandson. Initially meant as a parody of Back to the Future, Rick and Morty has become required viewing and a pop-culture sensation.
Misunderstood by much of its fan base, the show’s mix of smart writing and dumb humour has put it streets ahead of its competitors.
And now you can play it as a slot machine. Naturally, Rick and Morty appear on the reels along with parasite-mottled space rocks, Zigerion computer chips, and the portal gun that makes the show’s central conceit work.
It is a loving homage to a great show. Give it some play, my Glip-Glops.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics do a good job of mimicking the style of the show, though is rather short on the kind of in-jokes that make themed slots fun for the fans.
The animations are a little over simple. Disappointing given the quality of the animation on the show.
The music is a kind of elevator jazz rendition of the show’s theme song and neither lands as a piece of music nor as a joke.

Gameplay.text:
Rick and Morty Megaways is a six reel slot that uses the Megaways system by license. It also uses the cascade feature that is available for this system.
The Megaways system used by this slot is a licensed gameplay system created by Big Time Gaming that combines reels of randomised size with an any way wins system.
Every spin, the number of symbols on each reel is randomised between two and seven symbols. As a result, the number of win ways ranges from 64 (when there are two symbols on all six reels) up to 117,649 (for seven symbols on all six reels).
Reels two to five also have an extra row at the top which moves right to left during cascades. These reels have up to seven symbols including the symbols on the extra row.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus symbol.
Four or more Bonus symbols trigger the bonus feature. The player can then choose one of four bonus options. All the bonuses are free spin games. The number of spins is set by a randomiser wheel. The wheel has better numbers on it the more symbols the player hits.
The Mystery Free Spins bonus also uses the wheel to award one of the other three bonuses at random.
The three types of Free Spins a player can end up with are Pickle Rick Free Spins, Federation Free Spins, and Vindicator Free Spins.
Pickle Rick Free Spins start with a multiplier of x1. The multiplier increases by one after every winning cascade. A Scatter symbol is added to the reels. Three or more of these symbols add extra spins.
Vindicator Free Spins have special symbols added to the reels. These can be collected to generate additional prizes. Like Pickle Rick Free Spins, additional spins can be won by hitting three or more Scatter symbols during one Vindicator Free Spin.
Federation Free Spins have Clone symbols added to the reels. When these land, they turn their entire reel Wild. Additional spins can be won with three or more Scatters, as with the other spin options.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Ted is based on the Seth MacFarlane comedy movie of the same name, in which a teddy bear is brought to life by a childhood wish and grows up to be a foul-mouthed and lecherous pothead. The game does not capture much of the movie’s content, even though it does use some of the audio of Seth McFarlane’s lines.
Instead, the slot reduces the film to a few logos, some beer, and the bear. So much, then, for the theme.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The visuals are surprisingly poor for a licenced game. Although the graphics are high quality with plenty of 3D shine to them, the overall design matches them together poorly with a boring background and uninteresting set of symbols on the reel.
The animations are technically impressive, but again they suffer from uninteresting design choices.
The music is a small loop of film soundtrack that tires almost immediately.

Gameplay.text:
Ted’s base game is a classic five reel by three row slot with twenty win lines. This increases to a four reel slot in some of the free spin bonuses (details below).

Conclusion.text:
Despite strong source material and a lot of production value on show, Ted fails to charm in the way it should.
The graphics are top notch but the design is shabby, the gameplay is full of features but somehow seems dull, and the RTP is much too low to be enticing.
If you are a fan of the movie, you might be willing to forgive this slot's many weaknesses, but we are not.

title: Fortune Dragon
overview:

about_game: This high RTP (96.99%), high volatility slot offers fantastical dragons and decent bonus features.

Fortune Dragon review.text:
Fortune Dragon takes players to an East Asian fantasy world.
Under the watchful eyes of enormous Chinese dragons, players will begin to explore a beautiful palace. If they can stay on the right side of the majestic scaly beasts, players might discover a few treasures.
This slot is a great pick for those who are dreaming of an exotic adventure.

media.alt: Fortune Dragon - Free spins total win
media.caption: Total win in the Free Spins feature

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
A moody drumbeat adds tension to the atmosphere of Fortune Dragon. Meanwhile, the clatter of coins during spins creates a sense of excitement.
Players will immediately notice a pair of bright green dragons guarding the reels. They bare their teeth as their eyes glow, leaving no doubt that they will defend their treasure at all costs. Players will be left feeling curious and intrigued to understand these titular characters.
The symbols include a luxurious range of objects, including emerald and gold rings, red bags of coins, and elegant golden dragons. Letters and numbers with gilded frames also make an appearance.
The reels are situated in the courtyard of a majestic palace with large pillars on each side of the grid. Above the reels, players will glimpse a blue sky, giving the intense world a sense of optimism.
Overall, the sountrack and animation create an enchanted realm of Chinese cultural imagery and dragons.

Gameplay.text:
Fortune Dragon is a five reel, three row slot. Wins are awarded for landing matching symbols in adjacent reels. Winning combinations are calculated from left to right with 243 win ways in total.
The fast-paced gameplay of Fortune Dragon ensures that players will have no difficulty remaining engaged.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Free Spins feature begins when players land a minimum of 3 Scatters. Players begin the feature with a Free Spins Multiplier that can be as high as 10x and a total of 12 free spins.
All wins are multiplied by the Free Spins Multiplier except for five-of-a-kind Dragon symbol wins and Scatter wins.
Players can retrigger the Free Spins feature.
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. Wilds can land on reels 2, 3, 4, and 5.

media.caption: A Multiplier win in the Fortune Dragon slot machine

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.99%, well above our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The high volatility of Fortune Dragon makes this slot a great match for our preferred slot machine strategies. When selecting slots we suggest choosing the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable for the Fortune Dragon slot

Conclusion.text:
We recommend this high RTP, high volatility dragon-themed slot.
Mathematically-inclined players will adore the ample RTP and robust volatility of Fortune Dragon.
Meanwhile, the attractive animation and bonuses will make it easy for this slot to hold players’ attention.

title: Shadow of the Panther
overview:
Shadow of the Panther
    
        Play Shadow of the Panther demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Shadow of the Panther is as average as they come. Not bad, but also not very good.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Shadow of the Panther from High 5 Games is set in a kind of South American Jungle Book. A boy, face scarred by jaguar claws, seems to have been raised among the panthers of the Amazon.
Backstory is slim. Perhaps he is a twin, appearing on some reels as a double symbol. Perhaps he is a shapeshifter.
The Shadow of the Panther won’t ever fully explain itself to the player. Perhaps to allow the player to come up with the explanation for themselves.

media.alt: Shadow of the Panther base game win
media.caption: Slightly bigger win with up to 7 medium symbols

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The symbols look like they were culled from the covers of 1990s fantasy paperbacks. That strange blend of spray paint and photorealism with trippy neon colouring that made the animorphs books and Star Trek Voyager DVDs so distinctive.
The rest of the slot is a bit clunky. The visuals have not aged that well and the soundtrack is dull.
The whole slot looks and feels dated, and more than a little cheesy to boot.

media.alt: Shadow of the Panther stacked wilds win
media.caption: Wild symbol is stacked similarly to other symbols on the reels

Gameplay.text:
Shadow of the Panther is played on five reels with three rows and thirty win lines.
Most of the high value symbols come in a double format, which counts as two symbols towards any winning combination. This means the player can get as many as 10 symbols on a winline for the biggest wins.
Features are thin on the forest floor with one simple bonus game, no random features, and no gamble feature. This isn’t necessarily a bad thing, but it is worth taking into account if you’re a fan of more complex and varied slots.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Five or more Scatter symbols anywhere on the reels trigger the Free Spin Bonus. A double Scatter counts as two Scatters for this purpose.
Five Scatters give the player five spins, with each additional Scatter increasing the number of spins. Free Spins cannot be retriggered and use different reels.
Mystery symbols are added to the reels during free spins. Mystery symbols all transform into the same, randomised symbol at the end of each spin.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.0%, dead on our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.30 up to a maximum of $/£/€150.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium-high, which makes it a moderately good match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.alt: Shadow of the Panther base game paytable
media.caption: Full paytable in the base game

Conclusion.text:
Shadow of the Panther is underwhelming in almost every possible way.
The volatility is high enough to work with our strategies, but only just. The RTP is exactly in the middle of our rough estimate for average. And it has the exact minimum number of features to avoid being counted as minimalist. The visual style isn’t very good, but not so bad as to be distracting.
As a result, we can recommend this slot. But only barely.

title: Red Hot Tamales
overview:
Red Hot Tamales
    
        Play Red Hot Tamales demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: A simple, well-made slot but with a terrible RTP and low volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Red Hot Tamales is a hugely simplified three reel fruit machine style slot. It’s title is taken pretty literally in the theme with a few gestures at Mexican cuisine and a rather alarming volume of fire consuming everything on the reels and behind them.
Like many three reel slots, the theme is thin. But it really doesn’t need much substance. Simple slots like this lend themselves to simple set ups.
And in that regard Red Hot Tamales over-delivers.

media.caption: Win in the Red Hot Tamales slot

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Having been built in 2019, Red Hot Tamales has a slick and clean style. Hi-def, high frame rate animations that actually make it feel authentically old fashioned. The reels have a pleasant chunkiness that emulates a slot with actual physical reals.
The sounds lend themselves to this too. The music is mariachi band, playing over bells and tumbling sounds when the reels spin. When a win hits and the music kicks up a notch keeping things fresh.
The graphics are simple – fire in the background and sevens with bars on the reels. It’s an example of neat design that is high quality and uncomplicated.

Gameplay.text:
Red Hot Tamales is a three reel by three row slot machine. This makes it pretty compact on screen. The game has twenty seven win lines, which on a three by three slot effectively makes the game an any way wins slot.

title: The Price is Right
overview:
The Price is Right
    
        Play The Price is Right demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: If you like the show, you might enjoy this slot. But medium volatility and an RTP of 96.25% aren’t high enough for us.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The Price Is Right is an enormously long-running US game show. Initially founded in 1956, and revamped in 1972, for almost seventy years people have been coming up on stage to guess the price of various items to win prizes and money.
Only coronavirus could put a stop to it, and even then only temporarily.
In its most famous incarnation Bob Barker hosted it, but if you can’t get on the TV to meet him, you can now give this slot machine a go instead. It’s not quite the same as playing the show, but you won’t have to know the price of an above ground swimming pool to get lucky in this version.

media.alt: The Price Is Right slot win
media.caption: Win in The Price Is Right slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Given the long running nature of the franchise, it is almost bizarre how poor the front end of this slot is. The symbols look cheaply photoshopped together, although the background goes some way to replicating the cheesy TV show set look.
The animations cover up the visuals well and feel much more in keeping with the show, while adding some additional flare that is only available to the format of something like a slot machine.
These animations are nicely timed and coordinated with a simple musical track and some excellent spin and win sounds.

Gameplay.text:
Starting from a base game of a five reel slot with three rows and 25 win lines, IGT have also added a selection of features and bonuses that spice the gameplay up and make it more interesting than a first glance might suggest.
The Punch a Bunch feature can trigger before any winning base game spin. The player is allowed to choose up to four times from a set of hidden multipliers. Each time, the player may accept or reject the multipliers which are presented at random from a range running from x2 to x20.
The multiplier is then applied to the winnings on that spin.
For full details on the bonuses, see below.

media.alt: The Price Is Right slot & Punch A Bunch feature
media.caption: Pick a multiplier for your spin with the Punch A Bunch random feature
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus symbol.
Three Bonus symbols anywhere on the reels will trigger the Big Wheel Bonus. The player spins the big wheel, which can result in winning a multiplier, a Plinko Bonus, or Cliff Hangers Bonus.
The multiplier is applied to the bet per spin and awarded to the player immediately.
If the Plinko Bonus is triggered, the player gets three chips to drop on the Plinko board (a pachinko style board with prize values at the bottom). Each chip has a randomised multiplier that is applied to the prize value it lands on. The player then receives the total of the prize values with the multipliers applied.
If the Cliff Hangers Bonus is triggered, the player is awarded free spins with an increasing multiplier.

media.alt: The Price Is Right slot with Cliff Hanger free spins
media.caption: One of the bonus feature - the Cliff Hanger free spins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.25%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€500.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.alt: The Price Is Right slot high symbols paytable
media.caption: High symbols paytable

Conclusion.text:
With its weak visuals and interesting gameplay, The Price is Right is a game of many parts.
We like the varied bonuses, but dislike the volatility level. The RTP is pretty good, but not good enough to make up for the downsides.
Fans of the show might enjoy playing this slot, but we recommend something with a bit more variance.

title: Solar Disc
overview:
Solar Disc

about_game: Solar Disc is a beautiful but ultimately disappointing slot with an RTP of 96.01% and medium volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Borrowing its imagery from Central and Southern American cultures and wildlife, Solar Disc is a blend of the native American and American wildlife themes. There are plenty of slots in both categories but few that opt to combine the two together.
The background is a rose-tinted Peruvian plateau, reminiscent of the fields about Machu Picchu, while the foreground is littered with more coins than El Dorado. On the reels, most of the images are of animals. Bold pumas and spectacled bears. But there are also cups and ceremonial masks, stone keys, and ornate tokens.
Solar Disc is wild, magical, and has some of the mystical awe that the monuments of the Aztecs still inspire today.

media.caption: Win in the base game

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are Solar Disc’s first positive point. The animals are majestic and mounted on neat backgrounds with patterned frames that work with the theme and add visual spark.
The animations are bright and fun. And are not too over the top. They accentuate, without clouding the visual design.
The audio is where Solar Disc takes a dive in our estimation. Through a horrible error of sound mixing or a composer with a tin ear, the music is highly discordant and vexed by a cacophony of xylophone blows that seem wholly out of sync with the rest of the soundscape.
Turn the sounds off quickly and enjoy the views.

Gameplay.text:
Solar Disc is a six reel slot with four rows and 26 win lines. The player must gamble fifty coins per spin.
There is a free spin bonus, but other than that the gameplay is as stripped down and basic as they come.
There is no gamble feature.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus symbol and the Solar Disc symbol. If the player lands 24 Wilds (covering every spot on the reels), they receive 25,000 times their bet per line.
The Solar Disc symbol is turned over at the end of a spin. It will reveal one regular symbol. All examples of that symbol are then turned into Wilds and wins are calculated.
If a Bonus symbol lands along with a Solar Disc, the Free Spins Bonus is triggered. Bonus symbols can only land on reel one.
The Free Spin Bonus consists of ten free spins. During the free spins, a Solar Disc symbol will land on the reels every spin.

media.alt: Solar Disc symbol turns into wild symbols
media.caption: Solar Disc symbol turns random symbol from reels into the Wild symbols
Huge win in the Solar Disc free spins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.01%, almost exactly equal to our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.50 up to a maximum of $/£/€500.00 per spin. That is a high minimum bet, and a huge maximum bet making this a game for mid to high stakes players. Though your mileage may vary with your preferred site.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility. And the average RTP here is insufficient to make up for such low variance.

media.caption: Top symbols paytable for Solar Disc slot

Conclusion.text:
Solar Disc is beautiful to look at and plays smoothly, even if the gameplay is a little simple.
But its audio leaves a lot to be desired and the medium volatility makes it unhelpful to any player using our preferred slot machine strategies.
An average RTP isn’t bad but doesn’t save this slot or gain it our recommendation.

overview:

about_game: The Elephant King rules a dying kingdom, you must try to make your living in the desert with a medium volatility and RTP of 96.02%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Like IGT’s other Animal Kingdom slots, in particular their wide ranging "Buffalo King" franchise, Elephant King is a natural history based slot. This time the setting is sub-Saharan Africa in the dry season.
The ground is cracked and dry, the acacia trees are struggling in the heat. And across the land, a herd of elephants wander past zebras, rhinos, and impala, in search of greenery and water.
As you play, you’ll be looking to find treasured combinations just as hard as the animals are trying to eke out their livelihoods in the realm of the elephant king.

media.caption: Big win with the high paying symbol

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are designed for a bigger screen (full screen on laptop rather than mobile phone sized), they look a bit busy and overly detailed on a smaller screen. However, at a decent size they’re a pretty good example of the sort of pseudo spray paint style that dominates animal based slot art.
The animations and sound feel a little more up to date than the graphics. The spin and win sounds are simple but elegant, same with the animations.
In the background, there is an ambient track that works atmospherically without winding up the player. Overall, it’s a decent set of designs.

Gameplay.text:
Elephant King has a five reel by three row base game. This also has an additional horizontal reel (called the Prize Disc) at the top that randomises certain factors to do with bonuses.
There are forty win lines running from left to right.
And there are two bonuses: a Free Spin Bonus and a Prize Disc feature (full details below).
It’s enough variation to keep things interesting. Though we would gladly trade one of these features for a bit more volatility in the base game.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols on the main reels except the Bonus symbol. Wilds appear only on reels 2, 3, and 4.
The Prize Disc at the top of the reel rotates from right to left by one space. If a Bonus symbol lands on a reel (the Bonus symbol is only on reels 1, 3, and 5), then the symbol on the Prize Disc above that reel is awarded.
If the symbol on the Prize disc is a number, the player is awarded that number of coins (based on their chosen coin value). If the symbol is a Free Spin symbol, then the player receives 10 Free Spins.
Free Spin reels are upgraded to pay out better. The Prize Disc has Extra Spin symbols added to it. Each time one appears on the Prize Disc, an extra two spins are awarded, up to a maximum of 250.

media.alt: Elephant King win with the bonus symbol
media.caption: Bonus symbol win in the Elephant King slot machine

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.02%, spot on our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.75 up to a maximum of $/£/€225.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a weak match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility, so we’d really prefer bigger swings from this game.

media.alt: Elephant King base game & free spins paytable
media.caption: The paytable for base game and free spin showing the difference in payouts

Conclusion.text:
With a slightly clunky art style that only works when on a big screen, Elephant King doesn’t make the best first impression. Its animations and sound go some way to making up for this, but are not enough to impress.
The average RTP and medium volatility aren’t bad, but don’t get us enthused. And although the Prize Disc is a nice twist, overall the gameplay is a bit basic.
This slot might work for some players, but on the whole, we don’t have a strong recommendation for it.

overview:

about_game: Yet another Ancient Egypt slot with some fun gameplay to make up for middling style, volatility, and RTP 96.12%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Ancient Egypt. Again.
Rolling sands, golden death masks, pleasure barges, jewels, and an infestation of scarab beetles. This is the setting for Golden Egypt.
Eschewing the usual hieroglyphs in favour of a more varied array of artefacts and characters, Golden Egypt builds a vision of the Ancient Near East that is familiar to most slot players, but which comes with a few small twists.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are nothing special. The background is beautifully rendered Nile-bank real estate with pyramids and temples. But the reels are decorated with rather plain artwork. Realistic but characterless.
The animations are decent. Clean and simple movements to flag up wins, and smooth weightless spins of the reels.
The music is also short on atmosphere. It is made up of a perfectly fine ambient track. The win and spins sounds are solid too. But they could all be used on almost any kind of slot. There is nothing unique or engaging to make this slot feel different.

media.caption: Win in the Golden Egypt slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Golden Egypt is a five reel slot with four rows and 25 win lines.
There is neat Coins counter feature and a simple bonus. This is where the slot starts to make some room of its own.
The play feels familiar, but with enough spice to begin to make up for the bland visuals.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Bonus symbol. In the base game, Wilds appear when the counter at the top of a reel fills. When this happens, the next spin removes a Gold Coin from the counter and the entire reel comes up Wild. This continues until the Gold Coins run out.
The Gold Coin symbol on a reel adds a Gold Coin to the counter of that reel. The player begins with two randomly assigned coins on separate reels. There is room for two Gold Coins on each counter.
Three or more Bonus symbols trigger a Free Spin bonus. The player can choose between low, medium, and high variance options. The low variance option gives the player one random reel of Wilds each spin, the medium variance gives the player two, and the high variance gives the player three.
The number of free spins is correspondingly adjusted. With more spins in the low variance option, and fewer spins the higher the variance.
For example, three Bonus symbols get the player five spins with three Wild reels, fifteen spins with two Wild reels, or thirty spins with one Wild reel. Four Bonus symbols award twice the number of spins at each level of variance. Five Bonus symbols triple the number of spins.
We like high variance options, so recommend going for the few spins with more Wild reels.

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.18%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€500.00 per spin.
IGT lists the volatility of this game as medium. Medium volatility makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Golden Egypt slot machine

Conclusion.text:
With its medium volatility and uninspiring visuals, this slot isn’t doing a lot at first glance to attract us.
However, players who do not mind lower volatility shouldn’t be put off. The gameplay is fun and clever, the RTP is perfectly fine, and the design is solid if a little underwhelming.
While this doesn’t get a strong recommendation from us, its popularity means it is clearly working for a subset of players. You’d have to give it a try to see if you are one of them.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Pirates are a popular outlaw figurehead, and one that gets plenty of play in slot machines. The idea of hidden treasure and high-seas adventure is a heady one, that attracts many players to games like Pirate Kingdom Megaways.
With an ocean setting and suitably piratical probs as symbols on the reels, this is the slot all wannabe swashbucklers will be looking to play.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
With its flotsam and jetsam of barrels in the background and a sail ship bearing down, Pirate Kingdom Megaways does an excellent job of giving players a peek at their pirate fantasy.
The reels include treasure chests and hardy seamen as symbols and the soundtrack is a mix of moody strings, waves, and cannon fire.
The animations tie this all together, making for a nice audio-visual experience that is original but familiar in equal parts.

media.caption: Ultra win in the Pirate Kingdom Megaways slot

Gameplay.text:
Pirate Kingdom Megaways uses a Megaways system for the base game.
The Megaways system used here is borrowed on license from Big Time Gaming. It uses an any way wins system to determine payouts. This means winning symbol combos must be on adjacent reels going to the right and starting from reel one.
During each spin, the size of the reels is randomised. Each reel gets between two and seven symbols. This results in the number of win ways falling between 64 and a maximum of 117,649.
There is also a fun bonus that can be bought into by impatient players, but no gamble feature. Overall the gameplay is solid, if not especially new or innovative.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols. Wilds can come with a x2 multiplier up to a maximum of three times in one spin. The multipliers stack, so three x2 multipliers mean that the winning.
The Bonus is triggered when four or more cascades are triggered in one spin. The player gets 8 free spins, with an additional 2 for each additional cascade after the fourth. During the Free Spins, four cascades in one spin add an additional two spins to the total.
There is a maximum of 22 free spins each time the Bonus is triggered.
During the first free spin, a multiplier of x1 is applied. At the end of each spin, the multiplier increases by one. The multiplier applies only to subsequent wins.
During free spins, whenever a reel lands with seven symbols on it, then that reel is locked as a seven symbol reel. The reel still spins but it will have seven symbols on it for the remainder of the Bonus.

media.caption: Multiplier increases by one at the end of each Free Spin

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.20%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€40.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a great match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.
Buying directly into the free spins results in higher volatility but, depending on your jurisdiction, it also reduces the RTP to between 95.72% and 96.12%.

media.caption: High paying symbols of the Pirate Kingdom Megaways slot machine

Conclusion.text:
Pirate Kingdom Megaways is a rollicking seaborne adventure with pirates/, sunken treasure, and musket shot.
The theme is fun, the visuals and music are engaging, and the gameplay is everything you’d expect from a slot with the Megaways branding in its name.
The strongest plus for this slot though is the above average RTP (96.20%) and the high volatility. This combination makes it a great slot to use with our slot strategies.

about_game: Wrap up warm for a little ice fishing in this cartoonish slot with an RTP of 96.05% and high volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Ice fishing is an uncomfortable sport in which people traipse out onto frozen over bodies of water, drill a hole in the ice and drop their hooks through. If you like the sound of that, but would rather miss out on the hypothermia, Fishin' For Gold has you covered.
In place of fish, players are looking to land coins, and instead of dropping the lines themselves, a cast of anthropomorphised penguins, polar bears, walruses and – for some unfathomable reason – lions do the fishing on the player’s behalf.
This allows players to have a pleasant outdoor excursion without getting up from their couch.

media.alt: Fishin' For Gold slot big win

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are excellent. Plenty of time, effort, and digital paint was clearly spent on making the characters have some personality, while the background details work with the reels to create a sense of setting.
The animations are not fancy, but they do their job with admirable solidity and clarity.
The music is rather annoying after it loops a few times, though the spin and win sounds are nice enough, they add little and do not especially help the slot feel coherent.

Gameplay.text:
Fishin' For Gold is a five reel, three row slot with twenty five win lines.
There is no gamble feature, but the bonus wheel (described below) creates a constant sense of progress and allows for regular opportunities to switch things up.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
In Fishin' For Gold’s base game, there is no Wild symbol. There is however a Scatter symbol.
The Scatter only appears on reels 2, 3 and 4. If the player lands a Scatter on all three reels at once, then the Bonus Game is triggered.
The game has a wheel which can be spun (at a cost equal to the player's current bet per spin). Landing the arrow on the green wedge of the wheel will trigger the Bonus Game. The wheel starts off with a 0% chance of winning the Bonus.
When the player lands two Scatters on one spin, the chance increases by one percentage point each time. The wheel can be spun at any point. After the player spins the wheel, the chance resets to 0%.
Should the player trigger the Bonus – either by spinning the wheel or by hitting three Scatters – then they are presented with a choice of fishermen. This fisherman will then hook a selection of symbols that award the player a randomised number of free spins or a symbol which will be Wild for the length of the free spins.
Additional free spins can be won by hitting three Gone Fishing symbols during the Free Spin Bonus.

media.alt: Fishin’ for Gold - Free spins bonus
Fishin’ for Gold slot - Extra free spins

The reasonable RTP and high volatility make it useful to players who are following our slot strategies.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Aztec Gold Megaways borrows its imagery from South American civilisations that existed before the Columbian Exchange. But it turns that imagery into a fantasy setting with some Mike Mignola style art and a god-like emperor-priest.
It puts one in mind of the Hellboy comics or Disney’s Atlantis, but with real Inca flavour.
Can you decipher the ancient myth, and find the City of Gold? That’s the story to unravel in this slot.

media.alt: Aztec Gold Megaways with cascade wins system
media.caption: Three main features of this slot are Megaways system, cascade win system and any-way win system

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
As is often the case with slots built on the Megaways licence, Aztec Gold is beautifully rendered. The software (and no doubt the investment spent licensing it) often seems to inspire the graphics departments of the slot studios that use it. The reels combine the boxy style of Aztec pictograms with the more cartoony style of modern cell animation. The result is something that just oozes adventure.
The accompanying animations are detailed, and attractive. A winning combo triggers a proper light show, and everything is brilliantly coordinated with the music and sound effects.
The soundscape is all jungle sounds, pipes and drums, and the sound of rumbling stone mechanisms.
All in all, this is a slot with wonderful visual design and atmospheric sound.

media.caption: Big win in the Aztec Gold Megaways slot

Gameplay.text:
Aztec Gold Megaways uses the Megaways system, which randomises the number of symbols on each reel every spin. Here, the six reels can have up to seven symbols on them and a minimum of two. This makes for a range of win ways from 64 to 117,649.
Winning combinations are removed from the reels and new symbols drop in from above. Any new winning combinations from this cascade count towards the player's winnings for the spin.
There are a set of jackpots and a bonus game, which keep things interesting, though no gamble feature.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Five or more Scatters on the reel trigger Aztec Gold Cash Respin Bonus. Scatters come with a multiplier number on them or the word Mini, Major, or Mega.
During the Respin Bonus, all Scatters remain locked in place. The player gets three respins. Everytime a new Scatter lands on the reels, the number of remaining spins resets to three. At the end of the respins, the multiplier numbers on the Scatters will be added up and applied to the player’s bet per spin.
The Mini, Major, and Mega Scatters are worth a x30, x100, and x1,000 multiplier respectively.

Conclusion.text:
With a beautiful front end, Aztec Gold already holds a lot of appeal to your average player. The production value feels present in everything from the heft of the reels as they spin to the soundtrack music.
Behind the scenes it puts out a respectable 95.99% RTP and medium-high volatility. And a range of gameplay features that should satisfy the average punter.

For example, when key events occur, the reels move forward to emphasise the excitement, and recede as normal play resumes.
The music is impressive and varied depending on how well the player is doing at any given time. Overall, the design is a unified whole that works well to engage the player.

Gameplay.text:
Lucky Dragon is a simple three-reel slot. It uses the five straight lines as win lines, and wins are only achieved for three symbols, one per reel, on each win line.
With no bonuses, randomised features, or gamble games, this is a minimalist slot. That doesn’t appeal to everyone, but if it’s what you’re looking for, this game does it pretty well.

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:

title: Reel Rush 2
overview:
Reel Rush 2
    
        Play Reel Rush 2 demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Looking like a cheap version of Candy Crush, things don’t get much better when you get past the visuals in this low RTP slot.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Reel Rush 2 is a Candy Crush lookalike adapted to the style and form of a slot machine by NetEnt. It uses the same cutesy rounded images to tap into that highly addictive social media game’s popularity.
You probably already know if you’re a fan of that style. Or if it is something you can stomach.
As knock-off games go, it seems like a bad idea to remind players of a better game that they could be playing for free though.

media.alt: Reel Rush 2 base game big win
media.caption: Big win in the base game

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Reel Rush 2 manages to capture much of the tackiness of Candy Crush, while emulating little of the other game’s charm. Where Candy Crush’s bright boiled sweet rainbow was sickly sweet, this slot just looks sickly.
The reels are a washed out blue and the symbols rather blandly colourful. The animations are pretty good though, and inject some life into an otherwise moribund look.
The sound design goes some way to fixing the visual too. The bloops and pops make for a cheery feel to the slot. The music works well with all this. But the good aspects are dragging a dead weight uphill.

media.alt: Reel Rush 2 big win in Super Free Spins
media.caption: Super mega win in Super Free Spins feature

Gameplay.text:
Reel Rush 2 has a few interesting gameplay features up its sleeve. Although it initially plays as a 1-3-5-3-1 pattern slot, when the player wins, the reels increase in size with each respin. For example, the first respin uses a 3-3-5-3-1 pattern and the second a 3-3-5-3-3 pattern. This continues up to a maximum of five respins.
Wins are awarded for three or more matching symbols in adjacent reels starting from reel one. It doesn’t matter where in the reel the symbol falls.
This means the number of ways to win increases as the reels increase in size.
During the spins, between zero and three random features can be triggered. These include free super tokens, random Wilds, and – during free spins – additional free spins and multipliers.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols.
For every row that a reel expands by, the player receives 1-5 Super Tokens. These will be explained in just a moment.
There are several ways to trigger the free spin bonus. The most straightforward way is with the Free Spin Meter. For every two rows that any symbol expands on a spin, the Meter gains one star. This resets at the end of each spin.
When the Meter fills, the Free Spin Screen is triggered. In this screen the player has three options.
During Super Free Spins, a multiplier is added to all wins and increases by one with every winning combination. Some random features can also increase this progressive multiplier.

media.alt: Reel Rush 2 Free Spins gamble feature
media.caption: You can gamble your Super Tickets for a chance of getting Super Spins instead of standard Free Spins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.53%, which is way below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€40.00 per spin. A rather tight band that excludes low and high stakes players, though most bankrolls will be betting in that range.
The volatility of this game is at the high end of medium. This would make it a possible match for our preferred slot machine strategies, if only the RTP were not so low.

media.caption: Paytable for high paying symbols in Reel Rush 2 slot machine

Conclusion.text:
A mixed bag of visuals – poor images animated well – and a mixed bag behind the scenes – low RTP, highish volatility – make for a very borderline slot.
The fun range of bonuses and the twist of expanding reels make for solid gameplay. But in the end, this slot just doesn’t work for us.
It misses out on a recommendation, despite its widespread popularity.

about_game: Spooky ancient stones make up this atmospheric slot with an RTP of 96.72% and medium-high volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Secret of the Stones has an ancient look, reminiscent of the Ancient Britons’ and Ireland’s druidic past.
The secrets that the stones are hiding won’t be immediately clear, but the atmosphere and art style the theme allows is both intriguing and beautiful.
Grab your sickle, dig up some mistletoe and go dance around the singing stones. They’re calling to you...

media.caption: You can choose between two modes

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
A mix of Norse and Celtic styles make up this very pagan slot’s look. A beautiful mix of digital watercolours for the background and digital stonework for the reels. The Celtic knotwork and the stone animals have a unified style that works really well.
The stoney nature of the slot is amplified by well chosen reel sounds. The symbols fall with the sound of stones hitting each other and the music is eerie and ambient.
The animations are simple, but work very well with the theme and style of the slot. Overall this is one of the prettier slots out there.

media.caption: Base game win in the Secret of the Stones slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Secret of the Stones is a basic five reel slot with three rows and twenty-five win lines.
There’s a single bonus game that can be activated, though this has some variety injected by randomised features (see below for details).
There is no gamble feature.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. Wilds can be stacked.
Landing three or more Scatters anywhere on the reels triggers 10 Free Spins. Before the spins start, the player completes a picking game.
During the picking game, 20 stones are generated. The player picks one stone per Scatter they landed. Behind each stone is a random feature that will be active for the free spins or additional multipliers and spins.

media.alt: Secret of the Stones picking game
media.caption: Picking game offers 20 stones to choose from

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.72%, well over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%. A high RTP counts strongly towards a game’s recommendation.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.25 up to a maximum of $/£/€125.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium to high, which makes it a moderately good match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Paytable for high symbols of the Secret of the Stones slot

Conclusion.text:
Lovely to look at this slot is also a delight to play. The gameplay is simple but fun, and with an RTP of 96.72% it’s pretty cheap to boot.
Couple that RTP with the medium-high volatility and you’ve got a decent slot for our preferred strategies.
The main appeal of this slot is the atmosphere and visuals though and for them alone we’d give this one a recommendation.

title: Serengeti King
overview:
Serengeti King
    
        Play Serengeti King demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Welcome to the grasslands of Africa where by night you play the lion king and by night the panther queen. Great visuals, reasonable RTP (96.20%), and medium volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Serengeti King takes you to the African savanna where great cats rule. When the sun is up it is the lion’s turn. Majestic with his great mane he rules the day, but at night a black leopard takes the throne.
The conflict between these two rulers is cleverly integrated into the game's bonus system (see below). And their subjects – various animals including giraffe and meerkats – live on the reels.
Their realm of rolling grasslands make up the backdrop to the game.
It’s a great twist on the classic African wildlife theme.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
One of the selling points of Serengeti King is it’s excellent range of visuals. The reels are full of delightful animals that are both realistic and convey more personality than mere photorealism can.
The background is deep and beautiful. Grasslands rolling away for miles. The three settings for this are: day for the lion spins, night for panther spins, and dawn for the bonus spins are all gorgeous. And together they add up to a pleasing variety of visuals.
The animations are bright and clean. With a little more flare than most slots, but nothing too distracting.
The music feels like something off the Lion King soundtrack and the spin and win sounds are excellent. There is even a throaty growl every time a lion lands on the reels.

Gameplay.text:
Serengeti King is played on five reels with four rows. It has a fixed 26 win lines.
The game starts with Lion Spins, then after twelve Lion Spins it switches over to Panther spins. It switches back after another twelve spins.
During each spin, if a Lion or Panther symbol lands on the reels, it is collected. At the end of the Lion spins, all the collected Lion spins are added to the reels. At the end of the Panther spins, the same thing happens to the Panther symbols. You collect both symbols during all spins.
There is an excellent bonus (details below) and overall the gameplay matches the quality of the visuals and style.

media.caption: All Lion symbols are added to the reels after the full cycle of Panther and Lion spins are finished
After the Lion spins and then Panther spins are finished, collected Panther symbols are added to the reels for a payout
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol.
Three or more Scatter symbols trigger the Free Spin bonus with 12 spins.
If triggered by three Scatter symbols, the Free Spins start with zero on both counters. With four Scatters the player keeps their current count on both counters. With five Scatters +5 is added to each counter.
During the Free Spins, all the Panther and Lion symbols are added to the counters. At the end of the free spins, all of the symbols are added to the reels. Where a Lion lands on a Panther or vice versa, the symbol is transformed into a Wild and gains plus one to its multiplier.
You can buy directly into the Free Spins.

media.caption: All collected symbols are added to the reels for the final Free Spins payout

media.alt: Serengeti King - Free Spins big win
media.caption: Super Big win in the Free Spins feature

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.20%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100. per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable for the Serengeti King slot, set to €1 bet

Conclusion.text:
Serengeti King is a brilliant slot. From first impressions it gets across wonderful visuals in a rich and changing game world.
The basics of the gameplay are thematically strong, unique, and give the game a feeling of progress.
The RTP is a little above average, and we would normally like higher volatility to go with our strategies. But if you don’t mind taking a hit on the volatility, this is a truly excellent game that we highly recommend.

title: Honey Rush
overview:
Honey Rush
    
        Play Honey Rush demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Believe the buzz. This popular slot has some great features, a high RTP, and even higher volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Honey Rush is all about bees. The reels make up a honeycomb, the symbols are mostly flowers, and in the background the shadows of bees buzz about in a way that made this reviewer try to shoo them off his screen more than once.
The bees may be dying across the world, but here on the internet they are prospering.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Honey Rush is an excellent example of slot design. The background is pleasant, thematically relevant, and simple enough to let the reels shine.
The reels come with sharp, well designed symbols that are animated with great slickness and enough flare to keep things interesting. Animations are clear, quick, and clean.
Coupling this with the pleasant music and fun sound effects, the overall design of this slot is hugely commendable.

media.caption: Big win in the Honey Rush slot

Gameplay.text:
Honey Rush is played on a hexagonal grid made up of smaller hexagons. During each spin, each small hexagon gets a symbol added to it. Winning combinations occur when five or more identical hexagons make up a group.
A cascade system is then triggered. Winning symbols are removed. And the symbols above fall down to take their places. New symbols fill the top row, and any new wins are calculated.
Honey Rush has some additional features to keep things interesting (these are detailed in full below). All in all, the gameplay is varied, fun, and paced to keep things buzzing.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Any non-winning spin has a chance of triggering the Worker Feature. This adds a winning cluster of 7 to 15 symbols to the reels.
A counter tracks the number of symbols that are part of winning combinations during a spin.
Getting more than twenty winning symbols in one spin (or its following cascades) will trigger the Drone Feature. This is like the Worker Feature but with no maximum cap. Additionally, a Sticky Wild is added to the reels.
Sticky Wilds substitute for any symbol. After a winning combination, the Sticky Wild moves one space in any direction before the cascade is triggered. Wilds can also come with a multiplier of x2 or x3. The multiplier is applied to any winning combination that includes the Sticky Wild.
At 40 symbols on the counter, the player wins another Drone Feature and Sticky Wild. Same again at 80 symbols. Hitting 160 on the counter triggers a Queen Feature, which adds a winning cluster of between 20 and 37 symbols.

media.alt: Honey Rush Queen Colony bonus feature
media.caption: Highest level of the bonus feature, the Queen Colony

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.54%, well over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin. This should cover most bet sizes, though ultra-low and ultra-high stakes players might have to look elsewhere for their kicks.
The volatility of this game is high, which, coupled with the high RTP, makes it a great match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Paytable for the high paying symbols

Conclusion.text:
The key appeal of this game is its high RTP coupled with its high volatility. But it backs these features up with excellent gameplay and thrilling bonuses.
The fact that it is well designed, well paced, pleasantly animated, and possessed of a great soundtrack is the icing on the cake.
The slightly unusual reels might not be to everyone’s taste, but for the majority of players we think Honey Rush will taste sweet enough.

about_game: Legacy of Dead combines solid gameplay with nice graphics and an RTP of 96.58%. We also like the high volatility and fun features.

Theme and Storyline.text:
The Egyptian Book of the Dead is evoked by the title of this slot, though in practice it is more or less indistinguishable from the innumerable other Ancient Egypt based slots that exist out there.
The game sports exactly the kind of necropolis backdrop you would expect, with hieroglyphs and braziers burning. On the reels, there are animal headed gods, sarcophagus death masks, and golden scarabs on stone monuments.
Venture into this game’s gloom, just beware of mummies.

media.caption: Win in the Legacy of Dead slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Legacy of Dead does an excellent job of not venturing too far away from the look of other popular games that have explored this theme (Book of Ra and Book of Dead spring to mind as leaders in this field).
However, it manages to subtly upstage its competitors with slightly sharper and more up to date visuals. The animations are uncomplicated and eye-catching.
The music is atmospheric and, unlike so many slot soundtracks, is designed to blend into the background and the win and spin sounds in a way that avoids the typical exhaustion that looped music can instil in a player.

Gameplay.text:
This slot sports five reels and three rows with ten win lines and a typical neat gamble feature.
Players can use the gamble feature to play double-or-nothing or quadruple-or-nothing with their winnings by picking either the colour or suit of the next card off an infinite deck. The vig on this feature is 0%, but it is a handy way to introduce additional volatility into the game.
There is also one bonus feature, a free spin bonus (full details below) which is par for the course on a slot like this.

media.caption: Gamble feature offering an increase to the already high volatility of the game
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols and acts as a Scatter symbol.
Should the player manage to land three or more Scatters in one spin, the free spin bonus will be triggered with eight free spins given to the player and a payout of twice the bet per spin for three Scatters, x20 for four Scatters, and x200 for five.
During the free spins, a regular symbol is randomly chosen. When this symbol lands on the reels, wins are calculated, then it expands to fill that reel.
Free spins can be retriggered. When that happens, eight free spins are added and also another regular symbol, up to all nine symbols of the game, is chosen as an expanding symbol for the remaining spins.

media.alt: Legacy of Dead expanding symbol in free spins
media.caption: Expanding symbol pays for all active winlines in free spins bonus

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.58%, a good half a percentage point over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per line of $/£/€0.01. If one plays all ten lines, the maximum bet was $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a great match for our preferred slot machine strategies, as we like to seek out high volatility games as part of our slot strategies.

media.alt: Legacy of Dead top symbols paytable
media.caption: Paytable for high paying symbols

Conclusion.text:
Legacy of Dead by Play'n GO does not carve out any new territory for itself in the large and overpopulated world of Ancient Egyptian themed slots. However, it does beat out the competition by doing it rather better. The visuals are sharpened up for this slot as are the various features.
Its biggest advantage, however, is that it has a reasonable RTP, where much of the competition has sub-96%, this game has 96.58%.
The high volatility also makes this a good game for anyone using our slot strategies, allowing us to offer this so hearty a recommendation that you could keep it in a canopic jar.

Gameplay.text:
Wild Frames is a seven by seven grid game in which winning combinations occur when five or more symbols land in a cluster (joined horizontally or vertically, not diagonally).
Winning symbols are removed and a cascade occurs where further symbols fall down from above.
Bonuses are managed by a counter on the side of the grid (details below).

media.alt: Wild Frames slot Wild Card feature
media.caption: Wild Card random feature can trigger after any non-winning game round

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:

As the Bonus Meter fills, it triggers bonuses. When the Meter hits 20, all high paying symbols transform into one matching high paying symbol. At 40, the Meter triggers three to six additional Wilds, which are added at random to the grid. At 60, all the low paying symbols are removed, triggering a cascade.
At 80, all Wild Frames are transformed into Wilds, with additional multipliers added for additional numbers on the Meter.

Add a high RTP, and here you have a great slot that we are happy to recommend.
