title: Great Rhino Megaways
overview:
Great Rhino Megaways
    
        Play Great Rhino Megaways demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Take to the plains of Africa in search of the great rhino in this solid Megaways based slot with high volatility and an RTP of 96.47%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Great Rhino Megaways is a safari themed slot, in which the titular rhino is just one of several beasts you can find. The reels sport laughing hyenas, tearful crocodiles, and pink flamingos.
The reels are decorated with the kind of pseudo-tribal chic that east african tourist lodges like to adopt. And the background is rolling grasslands with various fauna grazing away, in short animated loops.
It’s got everything you might need for a good safari, except the lions.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
Digital airbrush-style paintings make up the main art for this slot. It’s a style that fits. It is reminiscent of those wildlife identification books of the 1990s and works perfectly with a safari theme.
The animations are slick, in the way most slots with the Megaways system in place are. They are smooth and clean, with plenty of indication to the player of what is happening and why.
The music uses east African instruments to create an atmospheric track to keep the game engaging for the player.

media.caption: Base game win in the Great Rhino Megaways slot machine

Gameplay.text:
Great Rhino Megaways does a good job of zhuzhing up the Megaways format.
The Megaways system used by this slot is a licensed gameplay system that combines randomised reels size with an any way wins system. Each reel can have between two and seven symbols (plus an extra row of symbols on reels 2 to 5). The number changes for each reel, each spin.
There is also a cascade system where winning symbols are removed from the reels and new symbols drop down from above (or move in from the right in the extra row).
As a result, the number of win ways can be as high as 200,704 (for seven symbols on all six basic reels, plus the symbols on the extra row for an 7-8-8-8-8-7 layout).
The player can kick in an extra 25% of their bet per spin to double their chance of triggering the Free Spin bonus feature (full details below). Free spins can also be bought into directly for one hundred times the bet per regular spin.

media.caption: Big win in the Great Rhino Megaways slot
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. The Wild symbol only on the top row, limiting its appearance to rows 2 to 5.
Four or more Scatter symbols in one spin will trigger the Free Spin Bonus.
The player then gets a choice of three Bonuses with differing volatility. The more Scatters that trigger the bonus the better all three options are.
For example, four Scatters allows the player to choose between 15 spins with a x1 multiplier, 10 spins with a x5 multiplier, or 5 spins with a x15 multiplier. For five Scatters the number of spins is increased to 19, 14, and 9 respectively. The multipliers do not change.
There is also an option to randomise both the multiplier and the number of spins. This is the highest volatility option.

media.caption: Players can achieve the highest volatility by choosing the mystery option

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is between 96.47% and 96.58% depending on your operator, well over our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high, which makes it a perfect match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility and RTP.

media.caption: Full paytable of the Great Rhino Megaways slot machine

Conclusion.text:
With its high volatility and RTP, this slot is off to a good start with its basic stats.
That it couples this with interesting and varied gameplay and an atmospheric audio-visual style gets it our recommendation. The theme might be a little overdone, but here it is done well.
We highly recommend this slot.

overview:

about_game: Interesting gameplay and fun visuals of Piggy Riches Megaways fail to make up for its low RTP and medium volatility.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Piggy Riches Megaways appears to take the old Bolshevik slur of "capitalist pig" rather literally, casting before its porcine protagonists far more than just pearls.
The reels are adorned in cash, the background is a McMansion complete with ugly water features and dollar topped ionic columns. The whole slot oozes a mockery of tasteless wealth that feels almost as if it is directed, rather unkindly, at the player.
The tongue in cheek nature of the crassness is what saves the theme from being ugly and instead feel rather fun.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics are excellent with just enough flare to make them stand out, without overburdening the creators with the weight of 3D modelling.
The animations are fun and stand out without being complicated. They do admirably the job of keeping everything clear to the player.
The music and sound effects are in keeping with the theme, though players may want to mute the music after a little while as it can grate quite severely.

media.caption: Win in the base game

Gameplay.text:
Piggy Riches Megaways uses the Megaways system which has six reels. Each reel has a randomised number of symbols on it between one and seven.
Instead of using winlines, winning combinations are any sequence of symbols on consecutive reels starting from reel one. This popular system allows for up to 117,649 ways to win.
There is also a cascade mechanic in place whereby, after wins are calculated, the winning combinations are removed and new symbols fall down from above to take their place. Wins are then recalculated and any further cascades occur.
The game does not have a gamble game and sports just one bonus game (see below for details).

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter symbol. There are also MegaWilds, which can cover a full reel, and which can come with a multiplier that is applied to any winnings using that Wild.

overview:

about_game: Book of Demi Gods II is a mostly decent slot, though a little basic. We like the high volatility and average RTP (95.9%).

Theme and Storyline.text:
Book of Demi Gods II is a kind of stripped down version of Spinomenal’s flagship series of Demi God slots. It reused some of the artwork from the bigger, fancier Demi Gods games, including background art and some of the symbols. All downsized for a smaller gig on a smaller game.
That said, the Greek Gods make wonderful source material for slot machines. And Spinomenal’s take on them is fun, unique, and more than a little bit sexy.
You can’t have too much of a good thing.

media.alt: Book of Demi Gods II epic big win
media.caption: Epic big win in the base game

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The visuals are one of the big selling points of Book of Demi Gods II. The artwork for the backgrounds is dramatic and beautiful. All done in that style of digital art that mimics closely the look of oil paintings.
The animations are clear and flashy, and are accompanied with dramatic sound effects that are varied and exciting.
The music, too, is upscale. A movie theme style orchestral soundtrack that is atmospheric and unique, but ambient enough so as to fade into the background rather than grate on the ears.

Gameplay.text:
Compared to the other Demi Gods games, Book of Demi Gods II is pretty straightforward from a gameplay standpoint. Gone are the multiple bonus types, the maps, and the random features.
Instead, Book of Demi Gods II has five reels, three rows and ten win lines. There is no gamble feature and just the one bonus feature.
So it is more or less your standard slot, despite its fancy pedigree.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols.
The Wild also serves as a scatter paying out for three or more symbols anywhere on the reels. In addition to payouts from any winning combos or scatter payouts, three or more Wild symbols will also trigger 10 free spins.
Before the free spins start, the player must spin a wheel that picks which symbol will be the Expanding Symbol for the duration of the free spins. When this symbol lands on a reel, it will expand to fill that reel.
Free spins can be retriggered, awarding ten more free spins when this happens.
You can also buy your way into the Bonus feature directly for x100 of your bet per spin.

media.alt: Book of Demi Gods II expanding symbol wheel
media.caption: Spin the wheel at the beginning of free spins feature

media.alt: Book of Demi Gods II expanding symbol big win
media.caption: Player has a guaranteed big win whenever reels are completely covered by the expanding symbol

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The reo player of this game is 95.9%, close to our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.10 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is high. That makes it a good candidate for use with our preferred slot machine strategies.

media.alt: Book of Demi Gods II high symbols paytable
media.caption: Paytable for high paying symbols in the Book of Demi Gods II slot

Conclusion.text:
Nice to look at and listen to, Book of Demi Gods II is a little underwhelming once you start playing.
The gameplay is basic, the RTP a little low, and there is just one type of bonus.
The high volatility is nice, and overall it's not a bad slot. But you might want to check out some of Spinomenal’s other Ancient Greek games first.

title: Relic Hunters and the Book of Faith
overview:
Relic Hunters and the Book of Faith
    
        Play Relic Hunters and the Book of Faith demo slot online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. Expert review included.
about_game: Combining the worlds of Indiana Jones and Lara Croft, Relic Hunters brings a new spin to the Ancient Egyptian themed slot. It also has adjustable volatility and an RPT of 96.37%.

Theme and Storyline.text:
Where most ancient Egyptian treasure hunters tend to pick one of either the Mummy, the Indiana Jones, or the Tomb Raider franchises to pull their theme from, Relic Hunters and the Book of Faith boldly carves its own path… by doing all three.
There is a gun-toting, tank-topped heroine who works alongside a fedora-wearing archaeology professor in a leather jacket to counter the machinations of a fearsome linen-wrapped revenant in a North African setting.
That said, if you’ve played Book of Ra or any of its innumerable spin offs, this slot will have little that comes as no surprise to you. There are mummies, scarab beetles, hieroglyphs and a background of sandy dunes and sandstone ruins.

media.alt: Big win in Relic Hunters and the Book of Faith
media.caption: Big win in the Relic Hunters slot machine

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The main difference between this slot and the other Book of Ra style slots is that Wazdan bring their visual and acoustic flair. When Wazdan is at its best, this is the area they excel in, and Relic Hunters and the Book of Faith is one of their best products in this regard.
The safeness of the theme allowed them to pour a great deal of care into the imagery. The symbols all have a lot of character and pull of a cartoony style while still feeling high-quality. The overall visual feel is one of solidity and class.
The animations are clear and simple, just enough to make things visually interesting without feeling busy or overdone. As the reels spin, the soundtrack is made up of middle eastern instruments playing an upbeat tune. The spin and win sounds are well chosen and go well with the animations for each symbol.

media.caption: Gameplay video

Gameplay.text:
The game play has also been given a polish with a few nice additional features thrown in to keep things exciting.
The main innovation in the base game is a set of counters which, when full, trigger the two bonus games (full details below). These fill during the base game, which is a six reel, three row slot with twenty win lines. The win lines play both left to right and right to left, increasing the number of chances to win.
As well as two bonus games, there is also a gamble feature, which players can use to wager their winnings in a double or nothing coin flip at the end of each winning spin.

media.caption: Game offers a gamble feature to increase the volatility of the slot

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Relic Hunters and Book of Faith has a unique, counter-based bonus system.
The Wild symbol substitutes for all symbols except the Scatter, Bastet and Pyramid Exploration symbols.
When a Bastet or Pyramid Exploration symbol falls on the reels, it is added to the relevant counter. Depending on the number of coloured dots on the symbol, the counter is increased by either one, three, or ten. When the counter reaches twelve, the relevant bonus is triggered.
Filling the Bastet counter to twelve will trigger the Bastet Free Spins bonus. This is made up of five free spins in which five randomly distributed Wild symbols are overlaid onto other symbols. Special symbols do not appear on the reels during free spins, so they cannot be retriggered until the player returns to the base game.
When the Pyramid Exploration counter hits ten, the Pyramid Exploration Bonus is triggered, giving the player a chance to play a picking game with a cash prize that depends on how many credits and multipliers the player manages to find before advancing through the four levels.
Any Mummy symbols landing on the reels can remove one, three or ten symbols from one of the counters. Mummy symbols landing on reels one to three remove Bastet counters. If they land on the other reels they remove Pyramid Exploration counters.
Three or more Scatter symbols pay out an amount that increases the more symbols you hit. It will also trigger ten free spins with expanding symbols and walking wilds.
During Scatter Free Spins, the male explorer Wilds stay on the reels and move to the right with every free spin until they drop off the end of the reels. The female explorer does the same, but moving to the left instead of the right. If the male and female explorer meet on a reel, three additional free spins are added to the bonus.
A randomly selected symbol is chosen as the Expanding Symbol. When this symbol lands on three or more reels, it expands to fill the reel and pays out from any position.

media.alt: Bastet spins feature in Relic Hunters
media.caption: One of the bonus features of the game - Bastet Spins Bonus

media.alt: Wandering Wilds free spins feature in Relic Hunters
media.caption: Wild symbols wander between reels in the free spins bonus game

media.alt: Expanding symbol in Relic Hunters free spins
media.caption: Randomly selected expanding symbol before free spins bonus begins

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 96.37%, a little over our yardstick for average of roughly 96% and so a perfectly respectable amount.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.20 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is set by a button in the main game. We suggest setting it to the "high" setting as our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

media.caption: Full paytable for Relic Hunters and the Book of Faith slot

Conclusion.text:
With its classic theme, nice front end design and nifty gameplay mechanics, we are already pretty sold on Relic Hunters.
Then it adds in adjustable volatility and an above-average RTP and we are head over heels. This one is a real treasure that we strongly recommend.

title: Slingo Deal or No Deal
overview:
Slingo Deal or No Deal
    
        Play Slingo Deal or No Deal demo game online for fun. Enjoy free casino games in demo mode on Casino Guru. No download required.
about_game: This low RTP (95%), medium volatility slot is decisively not a deal.

Theme and Storyline.text:
This slot is themed around the classic game show Deal or No Deal.
Players will be met with a wall of numbers and options. After taking a moment to get their bearings, they’ll realize the parallels to the game show format.
From then on, they’ll choose their fate as they select a lucky number and decide what to risk.
The style of the reels attempts a festive atmosphere. However, players may find themselves missing the excitement of the titular game show.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The minimalist wall of numbers seems intended to imitate the style of a game show. Sadly, the result is a dull design missing all the glitz and charisma of Deal or No Deal’s hosts and atmosphere.
Players could be forgiven for arriving at this slot and feeling as if they opened a program to complete their accounting. There is little to add spark, and even the colourful Joker symbol seems out of place, and a little creepy.
The cheerful background music and chiming sound effects do most of the work to make this slot engaging. Playing with the sound off quickly begins to feel like work, and players will definitely want to keep the music on. Without it they may find their minds wandering.

media.alt: Slingo Deal Or No Deal pick a box and start spinning
media.caption: Pick a box at the start of the game and start spinning

Gameplay.text:
Slingo Deal or No Deal has a single reel that spins in conjunction with a 5x5 grid of prize boxes.
There are a total of 12 win lines and 11 awards players may win.
Players begin this game by choosing their ‘Lucky Box’ and then spinning to match numbers on the reel with a selection of boxes on a grid.
Each time a player is awarded Slingo, this moves them higher up a ladder towards prizes. It also multiplies the value of remaining prizes.
The gameplay is unique and interactive. Players looking for something new and different may enjoy experimenting with this slot.
The game’s instructions also come with some handy tips for strategies specific to the game for players to optimize their chances.

media.alt: Slingo Deal Or No Deal - Banker's Offer
media.caption: Banker's Offer is available if you unlock at least 4 win lines
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
The Joker Wild symbol allows players to open any box in the column where it appears.
The Sugar Joker Wild symbol can be used to open any box in the grid.
Free Spin symbols award players additional spins at the end of a game.
The Devil symbol blocks players from potential matches.
When players get four Slingos, they unlock the Banker's Offer to which they can respond: Deal, No Deal, or continue spinning.
Should players choose to keep spinning, the banker’s offer will appear after each spin when a box was opened.
If players arrive at a Full House on the prize ladder, their win is multiplied x20.

media.alt: Slingo Deal Or No Deal & Full House win
media.caption: Even with the Full House's x20 multiplier the lowest valued box is no win at all

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95%, decisively below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€1 up to a maximum of $/£/€100 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a less optimal match for our preferred slot machine strategies. Our slot strategies target the highest possible volatility.

Conclusion.text:
We do not recommend this low RTP, medium volatility game show slot.
The unengaging design does little to make up for this slot’s poor mathematical stats. The low RTP alone would be enough to avoid this game, but the dry design makes it especially appealing.
Fans of the original game show will likely be disappointed at how little of the excitement is captured by this slot. Players who are unfamiliar with the game show will have no particular reason to stop by this slot.
The gameplay is unique, but not enough so to justify the unpragmatic odds and lackluster front end.

  Irish theme centered around the idea of Leprechauns and the pot of gold they keep stashed at the end of the rainbow.
In Slingo Rainbow Riches, that theme is overlaid onto Slingo’s bingo style software.
It’s still all the classic style of Rainbow Riches, but with a completely different gameplay. For those who love the familiar atmosphere but are still looking for something to keep it a bit fresh.

Graphics, Sounds and Animations.text:
The graphics on Slingo Rainbow Riches are excellent. The Slingo software lends itself to interesting designs. The verdant green of the Irish countryside is retained here, while the old symbols and fonts have been repurposed to work with the new style.
The music and soundtrack are pleasant and not too irritating, and the win and spin sounds are on theme and timed well.
Animations are a little simpler than in the other games as the grid format has mostly numbers rather than symbols for the animators to play with, but the slot remains visually top notch.

media.caption: After 10 spins you can buy extra spins to continue your game

Gameplay.text:
The grid is randomised with numbers between 1 and 75 in each square of a five-by-five grid.
The player spins the Bingo spinner and a row of numbers and symbols appear at the bottom of the screen, one for each column of the grid. If the number from the spinner matches any of the numbers in that column, the number is starred out.
The player is awarded prizes for the number of horizontal or vertical lines of five they successfully star out, starting at five filled lines. Less than five lines means game over, unless you are willing to buy extra spins.

media.caption: Full line starred out
Gameplay video

Wilds, Bonuses and Free Spins.text:
Because of the unusual gameplay, the idea of Bonuses, Wilds and Free Spins work slightly differently.
Wilds allow the player to select any number in the column it lands under, while free spins, add a ball to the bingo spinner.
There are no bonus games.

media.caption: Hitting 7 star columns opens the Toadstool picking game

Bet Sizes, RTP and Variance.text:
The return to player of this game is 95.6%, a bit below our yardstick for average of roughly 96%.
The range of bets on the site we tested ran from a minimum bet per spin of $/£/€0.50 up to a maximum of $/£/€100.00 per spin.
The volatility of this game is medium, which makes it a poor match for our preferred slot machine strategies. If the RTP was higher, we might be willing to overlook this, but when combined low-RTP and lower volatilities make for a bad combination.

Conclusion.text:
Slingo Rainbow Riches is a high quality slot at the design level. The graphics are lovely, the theme familiar, the style cartoonish and engaging.
But under the hood a combination of low RTP and medium volatility make it expensive to play, and useless to work with our strategies.
We do not recommend this slot.
